properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 9 at 1:35PM MST until January 10 at 6:00AM MST by NWS Rapid City SD
properties.description:
A narrow band of moderate snow will develop across northeast
Wyoming into west central South Dakota tonight. The snow will
quickly end Friday morning.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 1 to 4 inches
with locally higher amounts possible near the Wyoming Black
Hills.

* WHERE...Northern Campbell County and Western Crook County.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 6 AM MST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM MST FRIDAY
